  "prompt": "Which countries recognize the Moroccan Degree in Medecine?",
  "response": "The recognition of foreign medical degrees, including those from Morocco, can vary significantly depending on the country and even specific medical boards or institutions within the country. Generally, Moroccan medical degrees might be recognized in:\n\n1. European countries that have agreements or equivalent standards with Moroccan medical education systems, such as France.\n2. Countries in the Middle East and North Africa.\n3. Some countries in Sub-Saharan Africa.\n4. Countries like Canada or the United States may recognize Moroccan degrees, but often require additional examination and certification processes (such as the United States Medical Licensing Examination, USMLE, or the Medical Council of Canada Qualifying Examination, MCCQE).\n\nRecognition typically involves various checks, including evaluations by equivalence committees, verification of credentials, possible additional exams, or supervised practice periods. Therefore, if one wants to practice medicine in a foreign country with a Moroccan medical degree, it's wise to check the specific requirements of the medical licensing board in that country.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, individuals should contact the health ministry or medical licensing authority within the country they are interested in.",
